The paper deals with differential privacy in data analysis, which is a topic in computer security (cs.CR) and databases (cs.DB). The specific application domain is social networks, which involves graph theory and algorithms (cs.DS) as well as machine learning and data mining (cs.LG). The paper also discusses techniques for constructing queries with restricted sensitivity, which is a topic in statistics and information theory (cs.SI).
